To the haters: Hi-res means high resolution. Which is defined by how close lines can be to one another and still be visually resolved. You can have something that is high resolution but still poor viewing quality, though more often than not the viewing quality will be substantially improved by the use of or implementation of hi-res recording/output devices. So when someone says Hi-Res TS all it means is that the TS, which is a TS AND IS NOT GOING TO BE BLU-RAY QUALITY

(cont)...is that the TS will be a slightly higher quality than the average TS. HOW ABOUT you understand what the fuck you're talking about before you go hating on people that put themselves at risk not only so you can watch these movies outside of theaters, but because they believe that all information, art and media should be free and accessible by anyone. Jesus H. Christ, I've been using Torrent sites for years and don't host because of my ineffective security, but that's about to change just so I can come down on ignorant little twats like you. THANK YOU FROGGIE, despite the fact that you have uploaded a 'shitty quality' movie, I recognize that it is YET IN THEATERS and I applaud your efforts, and the efforts of all that believe as we do. Fuck Trolls, and long may your oars grace the Bay.
